17 multiyear anniversary of the date of issuance. If a person possesses a valid annual,
18 two-year, or other multiyear hunting, fishing, or hunting and fishing combination license
19 at the time of sale of one or more annual, two-year, or other multiyear licenses with
20 identical privileges to the valid license, the new license or licenses shall become effective
21 when the original license expires and shall remain valid through the full applicable period.
22 The department may specify the effective dates and term of the following licenses or
23 permits:
24 (1) The Georgia waterfowl and migratory bird stamp to meet requirements of Code
25 Section 27-2-20;
26 (2) The free Georgia salt water fishing endorsement to meet requirements of Code
27 Section 27-2-20.1; and
28 (3) Any permit or requirement authorized by Code Section 27-3-29 regarding harvest
29 recording and reporting; and
30 (4) The Georgia turkey permit to meet requirements of Code Section 27-2-6."
31 SECTION 2.
32 Said article is further amended in Code Section 27-2-6, relating to trout license, Georgia
33 waterfowl and migratory bird stamp, big game license, and alligator harvest permit, by
34 adding a new subsection to read as follows:
35 "(g)(1) Effective July 1, 2026, it shall be unlawful for any person 16 years of age or older
36 to hunt turkey in this state unless such person has a Georgia turkey permit in his or her
37 possession in addition to all other required hunting licenses. Any resident of this state
38 may be issued a Georgia turkey permit at no cost, and the fee for such permit for
39 nonresidents shall be $100.00.
40 (2) By July 1, 2026, the department shall design and sell a collectible Georgia turkey
41 stamp. Purchase of such turkey stamp shall be voluntary and shall not be required in
42 order to hunt turkeys in this state. The board shall be authorized to promulgate rules and
